1
00:02:01,813 --> 00:02:03,246
What?

2
00:02:03,247 --> 00:02:07,250
<i>Who might be
interrupting me prayers?</i>

3
00:02:07,351 --> 00:02:10,888
<i>Oh, it's you patty.</i>

4
00:02:10,988 --> 00:02:15,325
<i>Well, why would you
be talkin' to me?</i>

5
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:17,861
<i>You know, i'm just
a poor cobbler.</i>

6
00:02:17,962 --> 00:02:19,962
<i>What can i do?</i>

7
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,335
<i>Ahh, i see.</i>

8
00:02:25,436 --> 00:02:27,770
<i>But, why me?</i>

9
00:02:29,707 --> 00:02:32,208
<i>Well, i'll do me best.</i>

10
00:02:34,045 --> 00:02:38,816
<i>Aye. Well, i've always had
a lot of faith in you, too.</i>

11
00:03:04,842 --> 00:03:06,842
Knock it off!

12
00:03:16,854 --> 00:03:18,155
Excuse me, sir.

13
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,555
How much farther?

14
00:03:19,556 --> 00:03:21,425
You're going to
erinville, right?

15
00:03:21,426 --> 00:03:22,392
Yes, sir.

16
00:03:22,393 --> 00:03:24,393
Oh, not
too much further,

17
00:03:24,395 --> 00:03:28,431
i'd say erinville is right
at the end of that rainbow.

18
00:03:28,532 --> 00:03:31,467
Got a pot of gold waiting
there for you, do you?

19
00:03:31,569 --> 00:03:32,602
Pot of gold?

20
00:03:32,603 --> 00:03:33,603
Well sure!

21
00:03:33,604 --> 00:03:35,072
Leprechauns hide
their gold

22
00:03:35,073 --> 00:03:36,439
at the end
of rainbows.

23
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,175
What's a leprechaun?

24
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:41,144
Why, i thought everybody
knew about leprechauns.

25
00:03:41,245 --> 00:03:45,048
A leprechaun is an elf from ireland
with special powers of his own.

26
00:03:45,149 --> 00:03:48,618
If you capture one he's got
to take you to his pot of gold,

27
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:50,888
and grant
you three wishes.

28
00:03:50,989 --> 00:03:53,890
But be careful, if you let him
out of your sight for one moment

29
00:03:53,992 --> 00:03:56,960
he's gone
and owes you nothing.

30
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:06,837
Do you think there's
leprechauns in erinville?

31
00:04:06,938 --> 00:04:13,376
I recall a rumor that there's
a leprechaun around erinville.

32
00:04:13,477 --> 00:04:16,846
But mind you,
it was just a rumor.

33
00:04:20,818 --> 00:04:22,386
Where did it go?

34
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:23,586
The rainbow?

35
00:04:23,587 --> 00:04:26,690
Don't be worryin'
yourself none, laddie.

36
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:28,825
I know where
we're goin'.

37
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:12,869
You don't think you're being
a little too obvious, do you?

38
00:05:12,970 --> 00:05:15,204
No. As a matter
of fact, i don't.

39
00:05:15,305 --> 00:05:17,040
It's part
of the plan.

40
00:05:17,041 --> 00:05:19,376
Seems to me the last thing
sam needs is a dreamer.

41
00:05:19,476 --> 00:05:22,713
Why don't you just
help me with the ladder?

42
00:05:28,352 --> 00:05:32,055
Why don't you just ask her to
marry you and get it over with?

43
00:05:32,156 --> 00:05:34,124
Cause she'll say no!

44
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:38,562
You two boys need to have
some faith. Learn to believe.

45
00:05:38,663 --> 00:05:44,868
She needs someone who has at
least one foot on the ground.

46
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:47,603
What she needs
is me,

47
00:05:47,705 --> 00:05:50,874
and fortunately
i'm available.

48
00:05:58,416 --> 00:06:01,585
Right on time.
See ya, boys.

49
00:06:04,321 --> 00:06:06,656
Good morning,
good morning!

50
00:06:06,758 --> 00:06:07,623
'Morning.

51
00:06:07,624 --> 00:06:09,624
The usual?
Yes, indeed.

52
00:06:12,963 --> 00:06:14,798
So Alex, what
kind of scientist

53
00:06:14,799 --> 00:06:16,499
are we studying
to be today?

54
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,968
An epidemiologist.

55
00:06:17,969 --> 00:06:19,036
A what?

56
00:06:19,037 --> 00:06:20,804
An
epidemiologist.

57
00:06:20,805 --> 00:06:24,841
Somebody who studies epidemics-
you know, like the black plague?

58
00:06:24,942 --> 00:06:27,276
Sounds pretty
serious to me.

59
00:06:27,377 --> 00:06:29,377
It is.

60
00:06:31,615 --> 00:06:34,618
Your niece and
nephew coming today?

61
00:06:34,719 --> 00:06:36,018
Yeah.

62
00:06:36,019 --> 00:06:38,088
How long since
the plane crash?

63
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:39,356
Almost 6 months.

64
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:45,228
Well, if anybody can help
them face reality, you can.

65
00:06:46,497 --> 00:06:48,497
I hope so.

66
00:06:48,566 --> 00:06:50,367
Ta, ta!

67
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,368
See ya.

68
00:07:31,508 --> 00:07:33,508
Come in.

69
00:07:33,544 --> 00:07:36,312
Getting settled okay?

70
00:07:36,413 --> 00:07:40,149
I'm glad you decided to
come up here for the summer.

71
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:43,619
Mom said being here was
like being in heaven.

72
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:48,892
So i figured maybe that will
make it easier for him to find me.

73
00:07:51,895 --> 00:07:54,497
Hey, you're going
to have a great time.

74
00:07:57,668 --> 00:08:01,571
And i'm sure you'll have
all sorts of adventures.

75
00:08:01,672 --> 00:08:02,706
Adventures?

76
00:08:02,707 --> 00:08:03,806
Well sure.

77
00:08:03,807 --> 00:08:05,275
Hey, just look out there.

78
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:09,279
Who knows what adventures
are waiting for you out there.

79
00:08:09,380 --> 00:08:13,650
Why don't you come
downstairs for a bite to eat?

80
00:08:13,751 --> 00:08:15,751
Okay.

81
00:08:28,332 --> 00:08:29,666
Are you coming?

82
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:31,934
Be right there.

83
00:08:57,361 --> 00:08:58,428
Becky?

84
00:08:58,429 --> 00:08:59,395
Becky!

85
00:08:59,396 --> 00:09:01,998
We were just about
to have some lunch.

86
00:09:02,099 --> 00:09:03,166
What?

87
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,268
I said we were just
about to have lunch.

88
00:09:05,369 --> 00:09:06,236
No thanks.

89
00:09:06,237 --> 00:09:07,503
Are you sure?

90
00:09:07,504 --> 00:09:08,738
I made some
chicken...

91
00:09:08,739 --> 00:09:10,173
i'm not hungry.

92
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:12,174
Okay...

93
00:09:34,432 --> 00:09:35,632
star gazing?

94
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:37,633
Yeah.

95
00:09:45,810 --> 00:09:48,578
Did you ever
see so many stars?

96
00:09:48,679 --> 00:09:51,081
There's the
big dipper.

97
00:09:51,182 --> 00:09:52,248
See it?

98
00:09:52,249 --> 00:09:53,650
Yeah.

99
00:09:53,651 --> 00:09:56,486
And there's
the north star,

100
00:09:56,587 --> 00:09:59,855
it's helped many a lost
soul find their way home.

101
00:09:59,956 --> 00:10:01,324
Really?

102
00:10:01,325 --> 00:10:03,626
Alex has
a telescope.

103
00:10:03,727 --> 00:10:06,830
Maybe tomorrow she can
show you how to use it.

104
00:10:06,931 --> 00:10:08,998
Okay.

105
00:10:09,099 --> 00:10:11,099
Okay.

106
00:10:12,436 --> 00:10:14,436
Time for bed.

107
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:20,977
Goodnight,
aunt sam.

108
00:10:20,978 --> 00:10:23,213
Goodnight,
honey.

109
00:10:23,314 --> 00:10:25,915
Goodnight,
ace.

110
00:10:32,623 --> 00:10:36,526
I sure hope dad knows
about the north star.

111
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:45,667
Vrooommm...

112
00:10:51,408 --> 00:10:52,708
ready for landing?

113
00:10:52,709 --> 00:10:53,476
Ready!

114
00:10:53,477 --> 00:10:56,312
Okay, here we go!

115
00:11:02,587 --> 00:11:03,819
Again! Again!

116
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:06,889
Sorry, Tommy. It's
time for me to go.

117
00:11:06,990 --> 00:11:10,026
Tell me what it's
like up there, again.

118
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:11,761
It's beautiful.

119
00:11:11,762 --> 00:11:15,130
You feel like you're floating
over and through the clouds

120
00:11:15,232 --> 00:11:17,667
and the earth's
real small below.

121
00:11:17,768 --> 00:11:18,969
It's heaven!

122
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:21,070
I wish i could
go up with you.

123
00:11:21,171 --> 00:11:24,273
We'll see to it that
you get your wish.

124
00:11:24,374 --> 00:11:27,343
When i get back,
i'll fly you up there.

125
00:11:27,444 --> 00:11:28,644
Promise?

126
00:11:28,645 --> 00:11:31,747
With ace as my
witness, i promise.

127
00:11:59,342 --> 00:12:02,278
Guys, breakfast!

128
00:12:08,452 --> 00:12:11,086
Hey, you're late.
The shop's open.

129
00:12:11,187 --> 00:12:14,090
Not to worry my dear
friend, not to worry.

130
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,692
All right,
i'll bite.

131
00:12:16,794 --> 00:12:18,794
Why aren't you
across the street?

132
00:12:18,796 --> 00:12:20,530
It's part
of the plan.

133
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,599
Today, i go in
a little late.

134
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,567
Each day
a little later.

135
00:12:24,568 --> 00:12:28,304
Til she misses me
and i won't go in at all.

136
00:12:28,405 --> 00:12:30,405
Yeah, so?

137
00:12:32,643 --> 00:12:36,445
That's the night
i ask her to marry me.

138
00:12:36,547 --> 00:12:39,082
I'm telling you,
it'll work.

139
00:12:39,183 --> 00:12:41,484
Ted, you
missed a spot.

140
00:12:51,161 --> 00:12:53,329
Good morning.

141
00:12:53,330 --> 00:12:54,297
The usual?

142
00:12:54,298 --> 00:12:55,798
Thank you
very much.

143
00:12:55,799 --> 00:12:58,001
Hello.

144
00:12:58,102 --> 00:13:00,770
Don't i get a "good
morning" out of you?

145
00:13:00,871 --> 00:13:02,005
Good morning!

146
00:13:02,006 --> 00:13:03,272
Who's your
new friend?

147
00:13:03,273 --> 00:13:04,573
My cousin,
Tommy.

148
00:13:04,574 --> 00:13:06,574
Hi, Tommy.
Welcome to erinville.

149
00:13:06,577 --> 00:13:07,810
I'm rick callahan.

150
00:13:07,811 --> 00:13:09,212
Are you
a policeman?

151
00:13:09,213 --> 00:13:10,780
No, close though.

152
00:13:10,781 --> 00:13:11,881
I'm a fireman.

153
00:13:11,882 --> 00:13:14,984
Ever see a real
fire truck up close?

154
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:18,054
Mine's across the street.
Want to take a look at it?

155
00:13:18,155 --> 00:13:19,222
Yeah!

156
00:13:19,223 --> 00:13:22,492
Come on,
i'll race you!

157
00:13:24,995 --> 00:13:26,429
Wait!

158
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:30,834
We keep some of our
emergency equipment in here.

159
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:34,437
This ladder will get us up as
high as 3 floors if we need to.

160
00:13:34,538 --> 00:13:36,572
More emergency
equipment here.

161
00:13:36,673 --> 00:13:38,207
What's
that thing?

162
00:13:38,208 --> 00:13:39,475
What, this?

163
00:13:39,476 --> 00:13:41,778
This is the main
water hook up.

164
00:13:41,879 --> 00:13:44,313
You hook this up to the
fire hydrant on the street

165
00:13:44,414 --> 00:13:46,382
with the hoses here.

166
00:13:46,383 --> 00:13:48,718
Jump up here and
i'll show you the cab.

167
00:13:51,788 --> 00:13:53,523
That's spot.

168
00:13:53,524 --> 00:13:55,457
We rescued her from
the top of a tree.

169
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:56,926
Found she
had no owner,

170
00:13:56,927 --> 00:13:58,094
so we kept her.

171
00:13:58,095 --> 00:13:59,962
Haven't seen
a mouse since.

172
00:13:59,963 --> 00:14:01,931
Never saw
one before.

173
00:14:01,932 --> 00:14:04,700
That may
be true, but...

174
00:14:04,801 --> 00:14:09,705
i see mr. Conners
has caught your eye.

175
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:11,073
Full of blarney he is,

176
00:14:11,074 --> 00:14:13,643
but he's loved
by the whole town.

177
00:14:13,744 --> 00:14:16,712
He's a leprechaun
if there ever was one.

178
00:14:16,813 --> 00:14:17,914
A leprechaun?

179
00:14:17,915 --> 00:14:19,915
There's no such
thing as a leprechaun.

180
00:14:19,983 --> 00:14:21,317
No such thing?

181
00:14:21,318 --> 00:14:22,652
That's right.

182
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:25,221
Fairies and all that
stuff are just made up.

183
00:14:25,322 --> 00:14:27,556
They don't really exist.

184
00:14:27,657 --> 00:14:29,258
How can you
be so sure?

185
00:14:29,259 --> 00:14:31,894
Because you can't
scientifically prove it.

186
00:14:31,995 --> 00:14:33,796
That may be true,

187
00:14:33,797 --> 00:14:35,797
but there was
once a time

188
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:38,568
when scientists couldn't prove
bacteria and viruses existed.

189
00:14:38,669 --> 00:14:40,736
They were laughed at

190
00:14:40,837 --> 00:14:43,205
'til the microscope
was invented, right?

191
00:14:43,306 --> 00:14:45,374
Yeah, you're right.

192
00:14:45,475 --> 00:14:47,743
That discovery
led to vaccines and cures.

193
00:14:47,844 --> 00:14:50,079
That's exactly right.

194
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:52,715
So don't be so quick
to disbelieve

195
00:14:52,816 --> 00:14:54,884
because you can't see
or prove something existed.

196
00:14:54,985 --> 00:14:57,086
You might miss
some pretty neat stuff.

197
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:59,588
Remember<i> belief</i>
precedes the miracle.

198
00:14:59,689 --> 00:15:01,457
Rick, i believe
in eating!

199
00:15:01,458 --> 00:15:03,459
Where's our food?

200
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:05,928
Uh-oh, gotta
go guys, i forgot!

201
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:08,330
See you guys later.

202
00:15:08,431 --> 00:15:11,567
I still say there's no
such thing as leprechauns.

203
00:15:11,668 --> 00:15:13,903
And i say there are

204
00:15:14,004 --> 00:15:16,004
and he is one.

205
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:16,772
Is not.

206
00:15:16,773 --> 00:15:17,707
Is too.

207
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:18,808
Is not.

208
00:15:18,809 --> 00:15:19,775
Is too.

209
00:15:19,776 --> 00:15:20,676
Is not.

210
00:15:20,677 --> 00:15:23,679
Mr. Conners is just
a nice old man

211
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:25,915
who tells stories
down at the diner.

212
00:15:26,016 --> 00:15:29,352
He is one, and
i can prove it.

213
00:15:29,453 --> 00:15:31,087
How?

214
00:15:31,088 --> 00:15:32,922
We'll capture him!

215
00:15:32,923 --> 00:15:34,923
Yeah, right.

216
00:15:38,762 --> 00:15:41,497
Then, we'll get our wish.

217
00:15:52,175 --> 00:15:54,343
I still say
he's a leprechaun.

218
00:15:54,445 --> 00:15:55,477
Is not.

219
00:15:55,478 --> 00:15:56,378
Is too.

220
00:15:56,379 --> 00:15:57,480
Is not!

221
00:15:57,481 --> 00:15:59,115
Is too.

222
00:15:59,116 --> 00:16:01,116
Look it up.

223
00:16:11,594 --> 00:16:15,898
An irish elf
who works as a shoemaker.

224
00:16:15,999 --> 00:16:17,500
See!

225
00:16:17,501 --> 00:16:20,002
A shoemaker?

226
00:16:20,103 --> 00:16:22,104
He keeps a pot of gold.

227
00:16:22,206 --> 00:16:25,775
Upon capture, the leprechaun
must disclose his location of gold

228
00:16:25,876 --> 00:16:29,178
and grant his
captors three wishes.

229
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:32,815
Told ya!

230
00:16:32,916 --> 00:16:34,916
Whoa!

231
00:16:59,109 --> 00:17:01,610
Stay down! Keep low!

232
00:17:01,712 --> 00:17:03,712
Hurry! Hurry!

233
00:17:05,148 --> 00:17:06,182
I see him.

234
00:17:06,183 --> 00:17:07,416
He's coming.

235
00:17:07,417 --> 00:17:08,951
Don't forget,
if he gets away,

236
00:17:08,952 --> 00:17:11,387
he doesn't have to
give us three wishes.

237
00:17:11,488 --> 00:17:12,721
I know, i know.

238
00:17:12,722 --> 00:17:15,624
That's if he's
a leprechaun.

239
00:17:20,397 --> 00:17:22,265
Don't!
He'll see you.

240
00:17:22,266 --> 00:17:24,266
But how are we
supposed to see him?

241
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:25,601
We should be
hiding over there.

242
00:17:25,602 --> 00:17:27,036
That way we
can watch him.

243
00:17:27,037 --> 00:17:29,371
Okay, but let's make it
quick so he doesn't see us.

244
00:17:29,473 --> 00:17:31,473
The next time
he stops, we'll run.

245
00:17:40,984 --> 00:17:41,918
What happened?

246
00:17:41,919 --> 00:17:43,453
I think he saw me!

247
00:17:43,454 --> 00:17:44,553
Are you sure?

248
00:17:44,554 --> 00:17:46,656
No, but he's
still coming.

249
00:17:46,757 --> 00:17:48,791
Then he probably
didn't see you.

250
00:17:48,892 --> 00:17:50,892
Let's go!

251
00:17:52,395 --> 00:17:54,430
Hoo hooo!

252
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:22,558
Halt!

253
00:18:22,559 --> 00:18:23,992
You're captured!

254
00:18:23,993 --> 00:18:26,295
What's this?

255
00:18:26,396 --> 00:18:28,564
Miniature bandits?

256
00:18:28,665 --> 00:18:29,999
We're not bandits.

257
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,767
But we know
who you are!

258
00:18:31,768 --> 00:18:32,935
And who might that be?

259
00:18:32,936 --> 00:18:35,104
You're a leprechaun,
and since we caught you,

260
00:18:35,205 --> 00:18:37,807
you have to take us
to your pot of gold

261
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:39,608
...and grant
us three wishes.

262
00:18:39,609 --> 00:18:40,909
A leprechaun is it?

263
00:18:40,910 --> 00:18:42,178
My, my Alex!

264
00:18:42,179 --> 00:18:44,747
I never realized
you were a storyteller, too!

265
00:18:44,848 --> 00:18:46,849
Tommy thinks
you're a leprechaun.

266
00:18:46,950 --> 00:18:49,084
Tommy is it?

267
00:18:49,186 --> 00:18:51,186
It's a pleasure
to meet you.

268
00:18:51,188 --> 00:18:53,222
Liam patrick conners,
at your service.

269
00:18:53,323 --> 00:18:56,892
What gives you this notion
i'm a leprechaun?

270
00:18:56,993 --> 00:19:00,062
And don't think you
can get away from me.

271
00:19:00,163 --> 00:19:03,899
I'm sure i couldn't, even
if i were a leprechaun.

272
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,634
I told you
he isn't one!

273
00:19:05,635 --> 00:19:07,170
I didn't say that!

274
00:19:07,171 --> 00:19:08,637
Then
you are one?

275
00:19:08,638 --> 00:19:10,206
And i didn't
say that.

276
00:19:10,207 --> 00:19:11,940
So are you a
leprechaun or not?

277
00:19:11,941 --> 00:19:14,610
What if i told you
i was an angel?

278
00:19:14,711 --> 00:19:15,811
Angels have wings.

279
00:19:15,812 --> 00:19:17,680
Oh they do,
do they?

280
00:19:17,681 --> 00:19:19,915
And what might
a leprechaun look like?

281
00:19:20,016 --> 00:19:21,350
Like you.

282
00:19:21,351 --> 00:19:24,386
You two have got me
in quite a spot here.

283
00:19:24,487 --> 00:19:28,323
If i tell you i'm not a
leprechaun you'll think i'm lying

284
00:19:28,424 --> 00:19:30,059
so i can be on my way.

285
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:33,963
Tommy, you can't
judge a book by its cover.

286
00:19:34,064 --> 00:19:35,764
Especially an old one.

287
00:19:35,765 --> 00:19:38,367
Huh?

288
00:19:38,468 --> 00:19:41,871
It's not what a person looks like
that makes them what they are.

289
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:43,739
It's the intent
of their hearts

290
00:19:43,740 --> 00:19:47,509
and the good they are willing
to do for others that matters.

291
00:19:47,610 --> 00:19:50,146
He's trying to tell you
he's not a leprechaun, Tommy.

292
00:19:50,247 --> 00:19:52,715
So you can't grant
me three wishes?

293
00:19:52,816 --> 00:19:53,916
No, i can't.

294
00:19:53,917 --> 00:19:57,386
If only we could find
the lost faeden...

295
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:59,188
the what?
The what?

296
00:19:59,189 --> 00:20:02,191
Surely you've heard the
legend of the lost faeden?

297
00:20:02,292 --> 00:20:03,625
What's a faeden?

298
00:20:03,626 --> 00:20:07,029
The faeden is
a small gold flute,

299
00:20:07,131 --> 00:20:11,133
the king of the fairies uses to
play the song of the creator on.

300
00:20:11,235 --> 00:20:13,836
It helps all the other
fairies see the glory

301
00:20:13,937 --> 00:20:15,937
and the wonder
and the beauty of life.

302
00:20:15,972 --> 00:20:19,275
And Tommy, it's also what
he uses to grant wishes.

303
00:20:19,376 --> 00:20:20,876
And it's lost?

304
00:20:20,877 --> 00:20:23,279
Aye.
That's quite a story.

305
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:25,447
You see, one day
the king of the fairies

306
00:20:25,548 --> 00:20:28,317
comes to me
with a special order...

307
00:20:28,418 --> 00:20:30,953
to make shoes
for all the fairies.

308
00:20:31,054 --> 00:20:33,522
They've got this
wonderful ball coming up.

309
00:20:33,623 --> 00:20:38,728
They're going to
have funny fireflies hanging...

310
00:20:38,829 --> 00:20:41,697
but that's another story.

311
00:20:41,798 --> 00:20:43,698
But anyway,
after he left

312
00:20:43,699 --> 00:20:46,669
i realized he'd left
his faeden behind.

313
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:50,673
I put it in me safe for
safekeeping awaiting his return.

314
00:20:50,774 --> 00:20:52,808
But that night,
as i was working late,

315
00:20:52,909 --> 00:20:56,912
a young man busts into me
shop and demands all me money.

316
00:20:57,013 --> 00:20:58,881
And i give it to
him, every cent.

317
00:20:58,882 --> 00:21:02,318
But that wasn't enough for him,
he wanted the faeden as well.

318
00:21:02,419 --> 00:21:04,686
I told him,
"it's no use to you"

319
00:21:04,788 --> 00:21:06,788
"since you don't know
how to use it."

320
00:21:06,823 --> 00:21:08,256
But he took it anyway.

321
00:21:08,257 --> 00:21:10,159
I chased him
as far as i could,

322
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,160
but i lost him.

323
00:21:11,161 --> 00:21:13,128
He got away from me.

324
00:21:13,129 --> 00:21:15,730
But he didn't get
away from the others.

325
00:21:15,832 --> 00:21:17,232
What others?
What others?

326
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,768
Why, the fairies,
of course.

327
00:21:19,869 --> 00:21:23,538
He tried to make his get away
through these fields and woods.

328
00:21:23,639 --> 00:21:26,142
But he never made it.

329
00:21:26,243 --> 00:21:27,343
What happened?

330
00:21:27,344 --> 00:21:29,912
Well, the police found
his body in the river.

331
00:21:30,013 --> 00:21:31,113
Poor soul.

332
00:21:31,114 --> 00:21:33,549
They never knew for sure
what happened to him,

333
00:21:33,650 --> 00:21:34,684
but i do.

334
00:21:34,685 --> 00:21:36,685
What?

335
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:40,055
C'mere.

336
00:21:40,056 --> 00:21:41,724
The pooka.

337
00:21:41,725 --> 00:21:43,392
The pooka?
The pooka?

338
00:21:43,393 --> 00:21:47,762
Shhh...! Aye,
an odd fairy that one.

339
00:21:47,864 --> 00:21:50,166
Comes at night
in the shape of a horse,

340
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:52,267
and beckons you
to ride him.

341
00:21:52,268 --> 00:21:54,103
But if you
mount his back,

342
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:55,804
he'll take you
on a death ride

343
00:21:55,805 --> 00:21:57,706
that you'll
never survive...

344
00:21:57,707 --> 00:22:00,575
unless you're one
of the bravest at heart.

345
00:22:00,677 --> 00:22:01,810
Wait a minute.

346
00:22:01,811 --> 00:22:03,545
If they got
the thief,

347
00:22:03,546 --> 00:22:05,546
then the king
got his faeden back!

348
00:22:05,548 --> 00:22:08,817
No lass, seems that he lost
it somewhere on the fairy ride.

349
00:22:08,918 --> 00:22:11,686
Then the fairies know
where it is, right?

350
00:22:11,787 --> 00:22:13,789
No, according
to the legend,

351
00:22:13,890 --> 00:22:16,325
this area is still filled with
fairies all looking for the flute.

352
00:22:16,426 --> 00:22:18,060
Really?

353
00:22:18,061 --> 00:22:20,896
Aye lad, and they'll
find it someday.

354
00:22:20,997 --> 00:22:23,566
But i kinda feel
responsible for it

355
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:25,667
and i'd like
to find it first

356
00:22:25,769 --> 00:22:28,537
so i could give
it back to the king meself.

357
00:22:28,638 --> 00:22:31,440
So i come here everyday
looking for it.

358
00:22:31,541 --> 00:22:34,710
It's here somewhere,
in these fields and woods.

359
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:37,246
But alas,
the going's slow because

360
00:22:37,347 --> 00:22:40,048
me eyes aren't
what they used to be.

361
00:22:40,149 --> 00:22:42,518
We could help
you look for it.

362
00:22:42,619 --> 00:22:45,020
It'll be like
a treasure hunt.

363
00:22:45,121 --> 00:22:47,121
Aye, you could
at that,

364
00:22:47,190 --> 00:22:49,458
and a fine treasure
we might find.

365
00:22:49,559 --> 00:22:51,193
But i don't know...

366
00:22:51,194 --> 00:22:53,962
look, look, look there!

367
00:22:54,064 --> 00:22:55,298
What do you see?

368
00:22:55,299 --> 00:22:56,865
I don't see
anything.

369
00:22:56,866 --> 00:22:58,000
Nothing?

370
00:22:58,001 --> 00:23:00,869
Trees.

371
00:23:03,006 --> 00:23:04,706
Only trees?

372
00:23:04,707 --> 00:23:07,876
And look,
what's that over there?

373
00:23:07,977 --> 00:23:09,578
Clouds!

374
00:23:09,579 --> 00:23:11,579
Clouds.

375
00:23:12,916 --> 00:23:14,316
And
that's all?

376
00:23:14,317 --> 00:23:16,952
What about
the wind? Listen.

377
00:23:17,053 --> 00:23:19,388
Did you hear 'em?

378
00:23:22,692 --> 00:23:24,626
Ahh, never mind.

379
00:23:24,627 --> 00:23:27,096
I can see i've
got me work cut out.

380
00:23:27,197 --> 00:23:29,298
You've got
a lot to learn.

381
00:23:29,399 --> 00:23:31,900
This is not a task for
the faint of heart, you know.

382
00:23:32,001 --> 00:23:34,270
I'm brave.

383
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:36,204
Are you now?

384
00:23:36,205 --> 00:23:40,642
The fairies don't want anybody
else to find the faeden.

385
00:23:40,743 --> 00:23:43,346
You'll have to be smart
to avoid their traps.

386
00:23:43,447 --> 00:23:44,713
I'm very smart.

387
00:23:44,714 --> 00:23:47,183
Aye, i knew
that about you.

388
00:23:47,284 --> 00:23:50,753
You'll have to learn to
believe in many wondrous things.

389
00:23:50,854 --> 00:23:52,955
These fields and woods
are full of things

390
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:55,024
you've never
seen or heard before.

391
00:23:55,025 --> 00:23:56,024
We'll learn.
We'll learn.

392
00:23:56,025 --> 00:23:58,025
You will?

393
00:23:58,094 --> 00:24:01,563
You'll learn.
Well, that's different!

394
00:24:01,664 --> 00:24:03,665
Why not, then?

395
00:24:03,766 --> 00:24:06,402
We'll meet
back here tomorrow,

396
00:24:06,503 --> 00:24:09,004
and that's when
our journey will begin!

397
00:24:09,105 --> 00:24:12,007
That is, if it's all right
with your mother, Alex.

398
00:24:12,108 --> 00:24:13,909
Let's see what
time it is here?

399
00:24:13,910 --> 00:24:18,380
Here, hold that.

400
00:24:20,550 --> 00:24:22,618
Ahh, it's
getting late!

401
00:24:22,719 --> 00:24:24,085
She's going
to be worried.

402
00:24:24,086 --> 00:24:25,087
Off with you, now.

403
00:24:25,088 --> 00:24:26,088
Go on, go on!

404
00:24:26,089 --> 00:24:28,089
I'll see you tomorrow.

405
00:24:31,428 --> 00:24:33,328
Leprechauns, is it?

406
00:24:33,329 --> 00:24:35,329
Well, why not?

407
00:24:36,499 --> 00:24:37,900
What?

408
00:24:37,901 --> 00:24:40,869
What do you mean you don't
like the way i'm doing it?

409
00:24:40,970 --> 00:24:44,606
I am a storyteller,
not a preacher.

410
00:24:44,707 --> 00:24:47,810
No, you can't put angels
with leprechauns and fairies,

411
00:24:47,911 --> 00:24:49,945
it would
ruin the story!

412
00:24:50,046 --> 00:24:52,681
Besides, you could play
one of the fairies.

413
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:55,217
Well, you've got
the wings for it.

414
00:24:55,318 --> 00:24:59,188
Ah, patty,
where's your sense of humor?

415
00:25:01,658 --> 00:25:03,658
So, how was
everyone's day?

416
00:25:03,727 --> 00:25:04,926
Great!

417
00:25:04,927 --> 00:25:06,395
We caught
a leprechaun.

418
00:25:06,396 --> 00:25:09,798
We snuck up behind a stump,
jumped out and caught him.

419
00:25:09,899 --> 00:25:12,334
That's great, honey.

420
00:25:12,435 --> 00:25:14,336
Becky, how was your day?

421
00:25:14,337 --> 00:25:15,437
Fine.

422
00:25:15,438 --> 00:25:20,008
Tomorrow take a book
and go down to the lake.

423
00:25:20,109 --> 00:25:22,144
I didn't bring any books.

424
00:25:22,245 --> 00:25:24,846
We can fix that.

425
00:25:26,316 --> 00:25:29,451
Mr. Conners said we could help
him look for the lost faeden.

426
00:25:29,552 --> 00:25:32,520
Then maybe the fairy king
could grant us three wishes.

427
00:25:32,622 --> 00:25:34,056
Could i be excused?

428
00:25:34,057 --> 00:25:35,724
The lost what?

429
00:25:35,725 --> 00:25:37,492
The lost faeden.

430
00:25:37,493 --> 00:25:40,729
A gold flute that
was stolen from him.

431
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:43,299
Could i be excused, please!?

432
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,067
What is wrong?

433
00:25:45,068 --> 00:25:47,068
I've had enough!

434
00:25:50,073 --> 00:25:52,073
You're excused.

435
00:25:54,978 --> 00:25:57,612
Can we please help him
find it, mom?

436
00:25:57,714 --> 00:25:58,881
Find what?

437
00:25:58,882 --> 00:26:00,348
The faeden.

438
00:26:00,349 --> 00:26:04,085
Look, i don't want you
two bothering mr. Conners.

439
00:26:04,186 --> 00:26:07,156
I know he
likes to tell stories,

440
00:26:07,257 --> 00:26:09,591
and they're nice to
listen to but you can't...

441
00:26:09,692 --> 00:26:11,527
but,
he needs our help.

442
00:26:11,528 --> 00:26:15,598
And besides it'll be
like an adventure. Yeah!

443
00:26:15,699 --> 00:26:18,500
I'll talk to him.

444
00:26:18,601 --> 00:26:20,601
Yes!

445
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,973
When did that happen?

446
00:26:24,974 --> 00:26:26,709
I'm on the phone.

447
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:28,443
<i>I needto
talkto you.</i>

448
00:26:28,444 --> 00:26:30,712
It's my aunt.
I got to go. Bye.

449
00:26:30,814 --> 00:26:32,814
Come in.

450
00:26:35,885 --> 00:26:37,052
I'm sorry.

451
00:26:37,053 --> 00:26:38,854
Just sometimes i get
so tired of hearing

452
00:26:38,855 --> 00:26:41,957
about what Tommy
and the stuffed bird did.

453
00:26:42,058 --> 00:26:43,092
I see.

454
00:26:43,093 --> 00:26:45,694
I seem to recall
a little girl

455
00:26:45,795 --> 00:26:48,329
who wouldn't go anywhere
without sebastian.

456
00:26:48,431 --> 00:26:49,998
That was different.

457
00:26:49,999 --> 00:26:51,567
You're right.

458
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:54,703
Sebastian wasn't the last
gift your dad ever gave you.

459
00:26:54,804 --> 00:26:57,606
Do you know why he carries
around that dumb bird?

460
00:26:57,707 --> 00:27:00,108
He thinks dad's
coming back.

461
00:27:00,209 --> 00:27:02,044
If he doesn't have
it, dad won't find him.

462
00:27:02,045 --> 00:27:04,646
Look, he's only seven.

463
00:27:04,747 --> 00:27:07,049
You sound just
like my mom.

464
00:27:07,150 --> 00:27:08,850
Why don't you just
make him understand

465
00:27:08,851 --> 00:27:11,620
that dad's never
coming back.

466
00:27:11,721 --> 00:27:16,591
I know losing your
dad still hurts,

467
00:27:16,692 --> 00:27:21,730
but i promise, in time
the hurt will heal.

468
00:27:21,831 --> 00:27:27,436
You may feel like there's
nothing left to believe in.

469
00:27:27,537 --> 00:27:32,474
Like there's a big empty
place in your heart.

470
00:27:32,575 --> 00:27:34,575
What am i supposed
to put in there?

471
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:39,615
I wish
i knew, becky.

472
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:43,686
I wish i knew.

473
00:28:01,037 --> 00:28:03,772
Good morning to ya.

474
00:28:03,873 --> 00:28:05,907
And what
have we here?

475
00:28:06,009 --> 00:28:07,276
A metal detector!

476
00:28:07,277 --> 00:28:08,476
A machine that...

477
00:28:08,477 --> 00:28:11,613
my, what a good idea!

478
00:28:11,715 --> 00:28:13,415
And that's not all.

479
00:28:13,416 --> 00:28:15,884
A map, so we know
where we've searched.

480
00:28:15,986 --> 00:28:18,620
Aren't you
the smart one?

481
00:28:18,721 --> 00:28:20,922
I'm glad you're
on this hunt with us.

482
00:28:21,023 --> 00:28:23,726
Look! Here's where we are
at the edge of the woods.

483
00:28:23,827 --> 00:28:26,328
We've got all this
area here to cover.

484
00:28:26,429 --> 00:28:27,429
Whoa...

485
00:28:27,430 --> 00:28:28,863
that's a
lot of area.

486
00:28:28,864 --> 00:28:32,233
Well, if you've got
something better to do?

487
00:28:32,334 --> 00:28:33,268
No.

488
00:28:33,269 --> 00:28:37,906
Tommy, today
you're the leader.

489
00:28:38,007 --> 00:28:40,341
Where we gonna go?

490
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,946
That way.

491
00:28:44,947 --> 00:28:47,049
All right, then...

